tle_-_geograph.org.uk_-_3507287.jpg/500px-Cardoness_Castle_-_geograph.org.uk_-_3507287.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/cardoness-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/cardoness-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/cardoness-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/cardoness-castle-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","medieval","atmospheric","hilltop","free-entry"]},{"name":"Orchardton Tower","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"15th century","rating":3.8,"reviewCount":280,"access":"free","description":"Scotland's only circular tower house — a unique architectural curiosity tucked into the rolling Galloway farmland. Charmingly small and perfectly formed.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/orchardton-tower.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/orchardton-tower-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/orchardton-tower-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/orchardton-tower-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/orchardton-tower-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","free-entry","medieval","remote"]},{"name":"Carsluith Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"15th-16th century","rating":3.6,"reviewCount":150,"access":"free","description":"A compact L-plan tower house in a quiet corner of Galloway, built by the Browns who were mixed up in every local feud going. Peaceful now, with views over Wigtown Bay.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/carsluith-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/carsluith-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carsluith-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carsluith-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carsluith-castle-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","free-entry","medieval","coastal"]},{"name":"Lochmaben Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"13th-16th century","rating":3.7,"reviewCount":210,"access":"free","description":"A massive royal fortress on the shores of Castle Loch, built by Edward I to control the Scottish borders and later rebuilt by James IV. The Bruce family's original motte lies nearby — layers of Anglo-Scottish conflict reflected in dark water.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/lochmaben-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/lochmaben-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/lochmaben-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/lochmaben-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/lochmaben-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/lochmaben-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/lochmaben-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/lochmaben-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/lochmaben-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","riverside","atmospheric","medieval","free-entry"]},{"name":"Morton Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"13th-15th century","rating":3.6,"reviewCount":85,"access":"free","description":"A lonely ruin above an artificial loch in the Nith Valley — where earls watched over deer parks and the ghost of a murdered regent lingers in the mist.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/Morton_Castle.jpg/500px-Morton_Castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/morton-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/morton-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/morton-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/morton-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/morton-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/morton-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/morton-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/morton-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","remote","atmospheric","dark-brooding","hilltop","medieval"]},{"name":"Lochinch Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"intact","era":"19th century","rating":4,"reviewCount":580,"access":"paid","description":"A 19th-century baronial mansion set in the magnificent Castle Kennedy Gardens, between two lochs in Galloway. The Stair family seat, surrounded by some of Scotland's finest landscaped grounds.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/lochinch-castle.jpg","tags":["well-preserved","gardens","gift-shop","tearoom-cafe"]},{"name":"Castle of Park","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"intact","era":"16th century","rating":3.8,"reviewCount":180,"access":"exterior-only","description":"A handsome 16th-century tower house in Galloway, built by the son of the last Abbot of Glenluce who acquired church lands at the Reformation. Reformed faith, unreformed ambition.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ce/Parke%27s_Castle_courtyard.jpg/500px-Parke%27s_Castle_courtyard.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/wiki-castle-of-park.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","medieval","atmospheric"]},{"name":"Comlongon Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"intact","era":"15th century","rating":4,"reviewCount":520,"access":"paid","description":"A massive 15th-century tower house in Dumfriesshire, said to be haunted by a green lady — a Murray bride who threw herself from the battlements. Now a wedding venue and hotel.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/ad/Comlongon_Castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/comlongon-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/comlongon-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/comlongon-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/comlongon-castle-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","haunted","wedding-venue","events-venue","atmospheric","dark-brooding"]},{"name":"Torthorwald Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"14th century","rating":3.3,"reviewCount":45,"access":"free","description":"A massive ruined tower standing guard over a Dumfriesshire village — where feuding Border families fought over stone and power for centuries.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Torthorwald_Castle.jpg/500px-Torthorwald_Castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/torthorwald-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/torthorwald-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/torthorwald-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/torthorwald-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/torthorwald-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/torthorwald-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/torthorwald-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/torthorwald-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","medieval","dark-brooding","atmospheric"]},{"name":"Dundonald Castle","county":"South Ayrshire","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"14th century","rating":3.7,"reviewCount":280,"access":"paid","description":"A royal tower house built by Robert II to celebrate becoming king, rising from the remains of a vitrified Iron Age hill fort. The layers here go deep — from ancient tribal stronghold to medieval seat of Scottish kings, with views across Ayrshire to the sea.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/Dundonald_Castle_20080424_-_from_south_west.jpg/500px-Dundonald_Castle_20080424_-_from_south_west.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/dundonald-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dundonald-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dundonald-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dundonald-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dundonald-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dundonald-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dundonald-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dundonald-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["hilltop","well-preserved","medieval","atmospheric","prehistoric","guided-tours"]},{"name":"Greenan Castle","county":"South Ayrshire","type":"tower house","condition":"ruin","era":"16th century","rating":3.5,"reviewCount":150,"access":"free","description":"A lone tower house silhouetted on a dramatic sea cliff south of Ayr — built on an ancient promontory fort with concentric ditches that predate it by centuries. One of the most photographed ruins in Ayrshire, dramatic at sunset, wild in a storm.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/greenan-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/greenan-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/greenan-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/greenan-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/greenan-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/greenan-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/greenan-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/greenan-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/greenan-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["cliffside","coastal","ruins-romantic","photogenic","atmospheric","prehistoric"]},{"name":"Dalquharran Castle","county":"South Ayrshire","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"15th century / 1790","rating":3.4,"reviewCount":55,"access":"exterior-only","description":"A Robert Adam masterpiece slowly crumbling in the Ayrshire countryside — where neoclassical elegance meets centuries of Kennedy family ambition.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Dalquarran_Mansion_-_geograph.org.uk_-_424754.jpg/500px-Dalquarran_Mansion_-_geograph.org.uk_-_424754.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/dalquharran-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dalquharran-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dalquharran-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dalquharran-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dalquharran-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dalquharran-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dalquharran-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dalquharran-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","atmospheric","victorian","gardens","photogenic"]},{"name":"Maybole Castle","county":"South Ayrshire","type":"tower house","condition":"restored","era":"16th century","rating":3.6,"reviewCount":180,"access":"paid","description":"A 16th-century L-plan tower on the High Street of a small Ayrshire town, steeped in the dark legend of Johnny Faa — the earl who supposedly murdered a gypsy king and imprisoned his own countess in its upper rooms. Recently restored from the at-risk register.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/maybole-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/maybole-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/maybole-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/maybole-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/maybole-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/maybole-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/maybole-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/maybole-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/maybole-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","atmospheric","dark-brooding","medieval","hidden-gem"]},{"name":"Drumlanrig Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"intact","era":"17th century","rating":4,"reviewCount":145,"access":"paid","description":"A magnificent pink sandstone palace in upper Nithsdale — the 'Pink Palace' of the Dukes of Buccleuch. Renaissance grandeur in a vast Borders estate with a world-class art collection.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Drumlanrig_Castle_-_geograph.org.uk_-_5090781.jpg/500px-Drumlanrig_Castle_-_geograph.org.uk_-_5090781.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/drumlanrig-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/drumlanrig-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/drumlanrig-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/drumlanrig-castle-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","gardens","museum","gift-shop","tearoom-cafe","kid-friendly","guided-tours","dog-friendly"]},{"name":"Barholm Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"tower house","condition":"restored","era":"16th century","rating":3.5,"reviewCount":28,"access":"paid","description":"A beautifully restored 16th-century tower house in the Galloway Hills, home of John Knox's protector. Baronial dignity in a gentle green landscape.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2c/Barholm_Castle.jpg","gallery":["https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2c/Barholm_Castle.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","medieval","atmospheric","remote"]},{"name":"Kirkcudbright Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"Medieval","rating":3.7,"reviewCount":52,"access":"free","description":"Scant remains of a once-important castle in the artists' town of Kirkcudbright. The MacLellans later built their magnificent townhouse nearby, which still stands.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/kirkcudbright-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/kirkcudbright-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kirkcudbright-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kirkcudbright-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kirkcudbright-castle-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","free-entry","medieval"]},{"name":"Sanquhar Castle","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"13th century","rating":3.4,"reviewCount":22,"access":"free","description":"Brooding ruins above the River Nith in upper Dumfriesshire. A Crichton stronghold associated with two famous declarations posted on the town cross.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Scotland.Sanquhar01.jpg/500px-Scotland.Sanquhar01.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/sanquhar-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/sanquhar-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/sanquhar-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/sanquhar-castle-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","riverside","atmospheric","free-entry","medieval"]},{"name":"New Abbey Corn Mill","county":"Dumfries and Galloway","type":"mill","condition":"restored","era":"18th century","rating":3.5,"reviewCount":28,"access":"paid","description":"A beautifully preserved 18th-century water-powered corn mill in the village of New Abbey, near the haunting ruins of Sweetheart Abbey. Working heritage brought to life.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/new-abbey-corn-mill.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/new-abbey-corn-mill-2.jpg",